Sven,

The thermal diffusion coefficient accounts for the so-called &quot;Soret&quot; and
&quot;Dufour&quot; effects which cause diffusion of heat due to gradients in mass
fractions and diffusion of mass by gradients in temperature.

See any combustion or transport book such as the following:

    &quot;Combustion&quot;  Warnatz, Maas, & Dibble
    &quot;Combustion Theory&quot;  F. Williams
    &quot;Transport Phenomenon&quot;  Bird, Stewart, & Lightfoot

These give a high-level, superficial treatment.  For more in-depth
treatment, consult &quot;The Molecular Theory of Liquids and Gases&quot; Hirschfelder,
Curtiss & Bird, or the wealth of literature on this topic.

James


